	<h1><%= content_for(:title, "About") %>About</h1>

	<p>At the <A HREF="http://chicagosummit.lgbthomelessness.org/">Chicago Summit on LGBT Youth Homelessness</a> in May 2014, community organizers realized the need for a website connecting LGBT homeless youth with resources already available to them.</p>

        <blockquote style="border: 2px solid #666; padding: 10px; background-color: #ccc;">“We don’t even know what’s available to us.” - Homeless Youth</blockquote>

	<p>At <A HREF="http://hackforchange.org/">The National Day of Civic Hacking</a>, May 31 - June 1 2014 at the <A HREF="http://www.adlerplanetarium.org/">Adler Planetarium</a> in Chicago, a 5 person team got together to create this website. <a href="http://twitter.com/alison985" alt="Follow @alison985 on Twitter!">Alison</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/nugentcodes" alt="Follow @nugentcodes on Twitter!">Janna</a>, <a href"http://twitter.com/d_chan42" alt="Follow @d_chan42 on Twitter!"> Kelsey</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/laurendorman" alt="Follow @LaurenDorman on Twitter!">Lauren</a>, and <a href="http://twitter.com/stuart_lynn" alt="Follow @stuart_lynn on Twitter!">Stuart</a> hacked this site together in order to help LGBT homeless youth find resources.</p>

	<p>Follow us on Twitter at <a href="http://twitter.com/lgbtqhomeless" alt="Follow @LGBTQHomeless on Twitter!">@LGBTQHomeless</a>.
